## Add-ons — extra pages, content, ongoing SEO

The two add-ons most clients take:

1. **Copywriting at £80/page.** Saves four to six weeks of back-and-forth. I write the body copy from a structured interview and your existing materials. You review and edit. Most owners take this for at least the home and services pages.

2. **Monthly maintenance at £40/month.** Plugin updates, security checks, backup verification, ten minutes of small content tweaks. If you don't want to think about WordPress after launch, this is the cheapest insurance available.

The [SEO retainer](/services/seo-consulting/) is separate — starting at £600/month — and isn't bundled because not every business needs it from day one.

## Timeline

- **Starter:** 2-4 weeks from content received to launch.
- **Standard:** 3-5 weeks.
- **Growth:** 5-8 weeks.

The biggest variable is content. If you have copy ready or commission the copywriting add-on, builds run at the lower end. If content is being drafted in parallel, expect the upper end.

## How payment works

Fifty per cent deposit on signed quote. Balance due on launch. No retainer, no monthly lock-in, no automatic renewals.

Bank transfer (Wise or HSBC), Stripe, or PayPal. UK businesses get a VAT invoice. International clients get a zero-rated invoice.

## FAQs

**Why is your Starter cheaper than the agency quotes I've had?**
Two reasons. One: I'm one person. There's no account manager, no business development team, no London office, no agency markup. Two: I work efficiently because I've built this exact structure dozens of times. Less risk, less waste, less padding.

**Why is your Growth more expensive than the £999 web designer down the road?**
Different product. The £999 builders use templates, no custom design, no SEO architecture, no schema, no Core Web Vitals targets. They work for some businesses. They don't work for businesses that need the website to actually generate leads.

**Can I upgrade from Starter to Standard later?**
Yes. The build is the same WordPress foundation — extra pages, schema and internal linking can be added for £400-£600.

**Can I downgrade Growth to Standard if my budget changes mid-project?**
Before development starts, yes. After design sign-off, the work is mostly done so a downgrade refunds little.

**What if I want something not in any package?**
Most projects do. Tell me what you need on the discovery call and I'll quote it as a custom build. The packages are a starting point, not a cage.

**Do you offer payment plans?**
Three-month payment plans (deposit + 2 monthly instalments) on request, no surcharge.

**Are these prices ex-VAT or inc-VAT?**
Ex-VAT. UK businesses are usually VAT-registered and reclaim it. Sole traders below the threshold pay 20% on top.

